30/10/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police announced on Monday (October 29th) that they broke up a crime gang that smuggled weapons.
Seven people were arrested in the operation, in which weapons, ammunition and instruction manuals -- written in Albanian -- were confiscated.
The arrests were made in the village of Bibaj, near the border with Albania.
Police were acting on a tip from the Security and Counter-intelligence Directorate.
(Dnevnik - 30/10/07;
MIA, Makfax - 29/10/07)
